<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-05-02T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-05-02T03:00:00-05:00" n="110" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d110">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.102S/1355: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-05-02T16:00:00+08:00">May 2, 1935—4
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received May 2—6:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>179. Legation’s 177, May 1, 3 p.m., second and third paragraphs.</p>
                        <p>Cunningham reports that he has discussed the matter with the Minister and
                            proposes to attempt to arrange for the inclusion of equal rights.</p>
                        <closer>For the Minister:<lb/><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lockhart</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>